This was the dedication offering of the altar, on the day when
it was anointed, by the princes of Israel: twelve silver platters, twelve silver bowls, twelve golden
ladles;

each silver platter weighing one hundred and thirty shekels, and each
bowl seventy; all the silver of the vessels two thousand and four hundred shekels, according to the shekel
of the sanctuary;
